Command.Name: AcquisitionArm
Command.ToolTip: Arm camera after Image Settings were changed and before an image is requested.

Integer.Name: AcquisitionFrameCount
Integer.ToolTip: If Acquisition Mode is "Multi Frame", set the number of images to request here.

Enumeration.Name: TriggerMode
Enumeration.ToolTip: If Trigger Mode is "On", select a Trigger Source. If Trigger Mode is "Off", frames are triggered in a "auto sequence" refered to the External Exposure Control Singnals section of the PCO Camera Documentation.

Enumeration.Name: TriggerSource
Enumeration.ToolTip: Select "ExtTrig" without or "ExtTrigAndAcqEnbl" with acquisition enabled for external trigger or "soft trigger" to force a trigger by software. For more information have a look at the External Exposure Control Singnals section of the PCO Camera Documentation.

Enumeration.Name: TriggerSelector
Enumeration.ToolTip: Choose a variant, if external trigger "ExtTrig" or "ExtTrigAndAcqEnbl" is selected. For more information have a look at the External Exposure Control Singnals section of the PCO Camera Documentation.

Command.Name: TriggerSoftware
Command.ToolTip: Click here, if your trigger source is "soft trigger".

Enumeration.Name: TriggerActivation
Enumeration.ToolTip: Trigger Activation as specified in PCO Camera Documentation. Refer to the External Exposure Control Singnals section a Dip-switch at the back-plate of the power supply is used for trigger activation.

Integer.Name: Width
Integer.ToolTip: Width of the ROI. Valid ROI settings range from 1/1 to WidthMax/HeightMax (WidthMax/HeightMax are dependent from the settings of format and binning). For more information have a look at section 4.2.8 of the SDK-Description-Manual.

Integer.Name: Height
Integer.ToolTip: Height of the ROI. Valid ROI settings range from 1/1 to WidthMax/HeightMax (WidthMax/HeightMax are dependent from the settings of format and binning). For more information have a look at section 4.2.8 of the SDK-Description-Manual.

Integer.Name: OffsetX
Integer.ToolTip: x0 coordinate of the ROI. Valid ROI settings range from 1/1 to WidthMax/HeightMax (WidthMax/HeightMax are dependent from the settings of format and binning). For more information have a look at section 4.2.8 of the SDK-Description-Manual.

Integer.Name: OffsetY
Integer.ToolTip: y0 coordinate of the ROI. Valid ROI settings range from 1/1 to WidthMax/HeightMax (WidthMax/HeightMax are dependent from the settings of format and binning). For more information have a look at section 4.2.8 of the SDK-Description-Manual.

Enumeration.Name: PixelFormat
Enumeration.ToolTip: Pixel Format as specified in GigE Vision standard
Enumeration.Description: Refer to the Pixel format section (p. 117)

Enumeration.Name: TimestampMode
Enumeration.ToolTip: None: no stamp in image; Binary: BCD coded stamp in the first 14 pixel; BinaryAscii: BCD coded stamp in the first 14 pixel + ASCII text; Ascii: ASCII text only.

Integer.Name: NumImgsInSeg
Integer.ToolTip: Click here to get number of Images saved in active RAM Segment.

Integer.Name: NumImgsInSegMax
Integer.ToolTip: Click here to get Maximum number of Images saved in active RAM Segment.

Integer.Name: NumImgRead
Integer.ToolTip: Image number of image to get from active RAM Segment.

Enumeration.Name: ActiveSegment
Enumeration.ToolTip: Select the Ram Segment to save images at.

Integer.Name: StreamPacketsB2BDelay
Integer.ToolTip: Packet Delay Time between two UDP-Packets in clock ticks. Clock rate is 100MHz.

Integer.Name: StreamI2IDelay
Integer.ToolTip: Delay Time between two frames in ms.

Integer.Name: R2RDelay
Integer.ToolTip: Delay in ms between two image request, if Acquisition Mode "Multi Frame" or "Continuous" is selected.
